headline: GS downgrades Genuine Parts on economic risks, upgrades AutoZone on resilience
summary: Investing.com -- Goldman Sachs downgraded Genuine Parts Co (NYSE:GPC) to "Sell" from "Neutral" while upgraded AutoZone Inc (NYSE:AZO) to "Neutral" from "Sell" citing differing levels of cyclicality and defensive positioning in the current economic environment.

headline: Genuine Parts Company to Report First Quarter 2025 Results on April 22, 2025
summary: Genuine Parts Company (NYSE: GPC), a leading global service provider of automotive and industrial replacement parts and value-added solutions, plans to release first quarter financial results on April 22, 2025. Following the release, management will host a conference call at 8:30 a.m. ET. The public may access the webcast and supplemental earnings materials on the company's investor relations website. headline: Genuine Parts Leads Our Selection Of 3 Dividend Stocks
summary: As the U.S. stock market navigates through a turbulent period marked by mixed performances and renewed tariff concerns, investors are increasingly seeking stability in dividend stocks. In such uncertain times, companies with a strong track record of consistent dividend payments can offer a reliable income stream, making them an attractive option for those looking to weather market volatility.
